es around the nature of trust. The authors link these abstract concerns to empirical analysis, involving interviews with service-users, practitioners and managers. This book will appeal to anyone interested in the concept of trust, including social science researchers and students, as well as practitioners, managers and policy makers working with vulnerable people.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMental health facilities. 0aMentally illxPsychology. 0aPhysician and patient. 0aTrust. 7aMEDICAL / Health Policy.2bisacsh1 aCalnan, Michael, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995z97831111962130 cprintz978184742889940uhttps://doi.org/10.56687/9781847428905?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781847428905423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781847428905/original  a978-3-11-119621-3  Bristol University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2013-1995c1995d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles